Vocabulary
  • pride
    A feeling of satisfaction at your achievements or the achievements of your family or friends.
  • prideful
    Having or showing arrogant superiority to and disdain of those one views as unworthy.
  • pride of lions
    A group of large wild animals of the cat family with yellowish-brown fur.
  • pride-of-india
    Tree of northern India and China having purple blossoms and small inedible yellow fruits; naturalized in the southern United States as a shade tree.
  • pride oneself on
    To feel proud about an achievement, skill, or special quality that you have.
  • pride of bolivia
    Semi-evergreen South American tree with odd-pinnate leaves and golden yellow flowers cultivated as an ornamental.
  • pride comes before a fall
    Something that you say which means if you are too confident about yourself, something bad will happen to show you that you are not as good as you think you are.
  • pride of peacocks
    A group of large birds, the male of which has very long tail feathers.
  • pridefulness
    A feeling of self-respect and personal worth.
  • civic pride
    Pride in your city.
